</tr><tr><td style="text-align:right;font-size:115%;padding-right:0.3em;"><div class="plainlinks hlist navbar mini"><ul><li class="nv-view"><a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Template:Greek_myth_(Hades)" title="Template:Greek myth (Hades)"><abbr title="View this template">v</abbr></a></li><li class="nv-talk"><a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Template_talk:Greek_myth_(Hades)" title="Template talk:Greek myth (Hades)"><abbr title="Discuss this template">t</abbr></a></li><li class="nv-edit"><a class="external text" href="https://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Template:Greek_myth_(Hades)&amp;action=edit"><abbr title="Edit this template">e</abbr></a></li></ul></div></td></tr></tbody></table>
<p>In <a href="Greek_mythology" title="Greek mythology">mythology</a>, the <b>Greek underworld</b> is an <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Otherworld" title="Otherworld">otherworld</a> where <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Soul" title="Soul">souls</a> go after death. The original Greek idea of <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Afterlife" title="Afterlife">afterlife</a> is that, at the moment of death, the soul is separated from the corpse, taking on the shape of the former person, and is transported to the entrance of the underworld. Good people and bad people would then separate.<sup id="cite_ref-1" class="reference"><a href="Greek_underworld#cite_note-1">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup> The underworld itself—sometimes known as <b>Hades</b>, after its <a href="Hades" title="Hades">patron god</a>—is described as being either at the outer bounds of the ocean or beneath the depths or ends of the earth.<sup id="cite_ref-2" class="reference"><a href="Greek_underworld#cite_note-2">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup> It is considered the dark counterpart to the brightness of <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mount_Olympus" title="Mount Olympus">Mount Olympus</a> with the <a href="Underworld" title="Underworld">kingdom of the dead</a> corresponding to the kingdom of the gods.<sup id="cite_ref-3" class="reference"><a href="Greek_underworld#cite_note-3">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup> Hades is a realm <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Invisibility" title="Invisibility">invisible</a> to the living, made solely for the dead.<sup id="cite_ref-4" class="reference"><a href="Greek_underworld#cite_note-4">&#91;4&#93;</a></sup>
</p>
